<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1682" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1682">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.114M69/150.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-11">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Ottoman authorities, without replying to my repeated requests for
                            surrender of captain of <hi rend="italic">Texas</hi>, began proceedings
                            against <pb facs="1429" n="1325" xml:id="pg_1325"/> him in the criminal
                            court, Smyrna, on the 9th instant. The Greek Consul, Smyrna, was
                            notified, and the Greek Dragoman attended the trial, which was postponed
                            until July 30. I have again protested and renewed request for surrender
                            to our jurisdiction.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>